The child had reportedly been swimming in the shallow section but got into difficulty in a deeper section of the lagoon. CAPE TOWN A young boy has drowned at the Wilderness Lagoon, next to the Wilderness Beach. The child had reportedly been swimming in the shallow section but got into difficulty in a deeper section of the lagoon.He was declared dead on the scene.Two children survived a near drowning at the same lagoon on Friday.The National Sea Rescue Institute s Craig Lambinon says, Despite paramedic s efforts at CPR the child was declared deceased on the scene. The body of the child taken into the care of the forensic pathology services. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)